The paper deals with the problem of recovering a subspace-preserving sparse representation of a signal, which involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), signal processing (cs.SI), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also cites several papers from these subfields. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
